## MetadataParamsCheck

**Severity:** error | **Type:** LiquidHtml

This check ensures that parameters referenced when calling `{% raw %}{% render %}{% endraw %}` or `{% raw %}{% function %}{% endraw %}` tags exist in the target partial. It works by inspecting the called partial and determining which variables it expects:

- **If the partial has a `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag**, only the parameters declared in `@param` entries are considered valid. Required parameters (not marked `@param {type} [name]` with brackets) must be provided.
- **If the partial has no `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag**, the check scans for undefined variables in the partial body and treats them as implicitly required parameters.

This check is complementary to [MissingRenderPartialArguments](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/missing-render-partial-arguments) and [UnrecognizedRenderPartialArguments](/developer-guide/platformos-check/checks/unrecognized-render-partial-arguments), which rely on explicit `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` declarations.

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}app/views/partials/greeting.liquid{% endcomment %}
<h1>Hello, {{ name }}!</h1>
{% endraw %}
```

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% comment %}Calling site — 'name' is required but not passed{% endcomment %}
{% render 'greeting' %}
{% endraw %}
```

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% render 'greeting', name: current_user.name %}
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
MetadataParamsCheck:
  enabled: true
  severity: error
```

## Disabling This Check

This check can be disabled for partials where dynamic variable passing is intentional and cannot be statically analyzed.

